# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We need to move from the number in first part of the colon to the number in the second part of the colon, meanwhile covering all the alphabets between that in first colon to the one in second colon. For an example :
K1 : M4
Indicates, in each column from K to M ie K,L,M,
We need to go down the column by 4 spaces hence the answer will be,
K1,K2,K3,K4,L1,L2,L3,L4,M1,M2,M3,M4
Below code is the Implementation of the same.

