# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1) Created a result vector to store and return the result.
2) Since numbers are present at the 1st and 4th index of the string, stored the numbers into another variables known as no1 and no2.
3) Stored the both characters into variables called a and b.
4) Created two variables max_n and min_n to store maximum and minimum of both the numbers in respective variables.
5) Iterated from a to b in external loop and iterated from min_n to max_n in the internal loop.
6) Kept concatenating and adding the string into result vector.


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<string> cellsInRange(string s) {
        vector<string> result;
        int no1 = s[1]-'0', no2 = s[4]-'0', max_n, min_n;
        char a = s[0], b = s[3];

        max_n = max(no1,no2);
        min_n = min(no1,no2);

        char j = a;
        while(j <= b){
            int i = min_n;
            while(i <= max_n){
                result.push_back(j+to_string(i));
                i++;
            }
            j++;
        }



        return result;
    }
};
```

