# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
It's an easy problem just need patience.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Extract the range of column and row, then start adding it to list storing the cells.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O( |col1-col2| * |row1-row2| )
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O( |col1-col2| * |row1-row2| )
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public List<String> cellsInRange(String s) {
        List<String> cells = new ArrayList<>();
        char col1 = s.charAt(0);
        char col2 = s.charAt(3);
        int row1 = Integer.valueOf(String.valueOf(s.charAt(1)));
        int row2 = Integer.valueOf(String.valueOf(s.charAt(4)));
        for(int i=(int)col1;i<=(int)col2;i++){
            for(int j=row1;j<=row2;j++){
                cells.add(String.valueOf((char)i) + String.valueOf(j));
            }
        }
        return cells;
    }
    // Time Complexity : O(|col1-col2| * |row1-row2|)
    // Space Complexity : O(|col1-col2| * |row1-row2|)
