# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- Idea is we will sort the flowers and we say ok we have some garden which are alredy full now I have `x` amount of extra flower 
- so till what we can push the minima of non full garden using `x` amount of flower .
- and in each iteration we will increase the number of full garden and naturally now `x` will decrease to `x'` and how again we do same thing as above and will calculate the  maxima of all result 
- we can get intial number of garden >=target using binay search 
