# Upvote if helpful 🔥🔥

# Intuition
```
When we look at the problem we can instantly say that 
it is coin change problem where we have only coins 
of 2 and 3 and we want to use minimum number 
of coins for the frequency of every element.
```

# Approach
``` 
first we will calculate the frequency of every value 
using map and store the frequency in another array.
after that for every element in that array we will apply 
coin change function which will give us minimum coins required
for every frequency in that array.
if minimum coins comes out 100005(ie >10^5) for any of 
the frequency then we will instantly return -1 
as the combinations of 2, 3 is not possible so no need to
calculate further.

Now CoinChange Function:
    base cases:
        if n is 2, 3 then we can just return 1 as 1 round will
        be enough for that frequency.
        if n==1 then we don't have any choice so have to return some
            larger value.

        for every frequency we have 2 recursive calls:
                i)either take coin of 2 (obviously if n>=2)
                ii)or either take coin of 3.
        take minimum between 2 and return to my parent call.

    while doing so we will store it in our dp so that if next
    time if same value comes then we will return the stored value.
```

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
vector<int>dp;
    int coinchange(int n){

        if(n==2 || n==3)return 1;

        //if(n<0)return 100005;

        if(n==1){
            return 100005;
        }

        if(dp[n]!=-1)return dp[n];

        int a=INT_MAX;
        if(n>=2){
            a= min(a, coinchange(n-2)+1);
        }

        if(n>=3){
            a= min(a, coinchange(n-3)+1);
        }

        return dp[n]= a;

    }
    int minimumRounds(vector<int>& tasks) {
        dp.resize(100005, -1);

        unordered_map<int, int>mp;
        for(auto i: tasks)mp[i]++;

        vector<int>arr;
        for(auto k: mp){
            arr.push_back(k.second);
        }

        int ans=0;
        for(int i=0; i<arr.size(); i++){
            int curr= coinchange(arr[i]);
            if(curr>=100005)return -1;
            else ans+=curr;
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```
