# Intuition
if freq(level) == 1
we cannot express in 3 tasks + 3 tasks + .. + 2 tasks

check for freq(level) > 1
and try to express in 3 tasks + 3 tasks + .. + 2 tasks.

so we should select the minimum number of 3 and 2.

we should select maximum of 3 tasks and at last add one (1 task or 2 task).

# Approach
if freq(level) == 1 --> return -1;
if freq(level) == 2 --> one 2-task
if freq(level) == 3 --> one 3-task

From observation, we can see that there's only 3 possible outcomes.

(A) If the frequency is 1, the task cannot be performed so we return -1.
(B) If the frequency is 3, the task can be performed and we return frequency/3.
(C) Now if the frequency is not completely divisible by 3, then the possible remainders are 1 and 2. Lets check them out:

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)

