# PreRequisite
Reader should know map STL.

# Approach
MAPPING VALUES AND THEIR OCCURENCE .FOR MINIMUM ROUNDS ,GROUP OF 3'S SHOULD BE MAXIMUM . 
THEREFORE ONLY THREE CASES ACCORDING TO OUR PROBLEM .

CASE I :
# **IF (it.second%3==0)**
Then ans+=it.second/3;

CASE II :
# IF (it.second%3==1)
Then ans+=2(2 group of 2's)+ (it.second-4)/3(remaining group of 3's);

example :
i. [69,69,69,69,69,69,69,69,69,69] 
Total number of 69 is 10 .
Now 10 can be divided into 2 group of 3's{6 elements} and
2 group of 2's{4 elements}.

ii.Let frequency be 40 then 40%3==1 .
Therefore ans+= 2(from 2's) +36/3 (from 3's)

CASE III.
# IF (it.second%3==2)
Then ans+= 1(1 group of 2's)+ (it.second-2)/3(remaining group of 3's)


# Complexity
- Time complexity:
 O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minimumRounds(vector<int>& tasks) {
        map<int,int>mpp;
        for(auto it : tasks)mpp[it]++;
        int ans=0;
        for(auto it : mpp){
            if(it.second<2)return -1;
            else{
                if(it.second%3==0){
                    ans+=(it.second/3);
                }
                else if(it.second%3==1){
                    ans+=2;
                    ans+=(it.second-4)/3; // 40 - 40%3==1 .therefore ans=2(from 2's) +36/3 (from 3's) 
                }
                else if(it.second%3==2){
                    ans+=1;           
                    ans+=(it.second-2)/3; //17%3==2. 17 - 3 3 3 3 3 2 
                }
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};

