# Intuition
As it frequency based question, we have to use map for it.

# Approach
If frequency of any task is 1. then return -1 because we can not do that task as we have to do 2 or 3 tasks in one go.

Now, all we have is the remainder if we devide particular frequency by 3.

If remainder is 1, eg. freq task == 4, then we have to do two round each of 2-2 tasks which is indeed ceil(freq task / 3).

If remainder is 2, eg. freq task == 5, then we have to do two round each of 2-3 tasks which is indeed ceil(freq task / 3).

If remainder is 0, eg. freq task == 6, then we have to do two round each of 3-3 tasks which is indeed ceil(freq task / 3).

This is it !!!

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$

- Space complexity: $$O(n)$$


