> **Get maximum by checking only single digit.**

**Intuition behind O(1) Space**:
In the question it is given that `a number is unique if all digits are same`.
So instead of **comparing subtrings**, we can simple compare single digit because **if(7<8) then (777<888)**.

**C++ VERSION O(1) SPACE**

    string largestGoodInteger(string num) {
        int ans=-1;
        for(int i=0;i+2<num.size();i++){
            if(num[i]==num[i+1] && num[i]==num[i+2]) ans= max(ans,num[i]-'0');
        }
        return ans!=-1? string(3,ans+'0') : "";
     }

**JAVA VERSION O(1) SPACE**

	 public String largestGoodInteger(String num) {
        int ans=-1;
        for(int i=0;i+2<num.length();i++){
            if(num.charAt(i)==num.charAt(i+1) && num.charAt(i)==num.charAt(i+2)) 
                ans= Math.max(ans,num.charAt(i)-'0');
        }
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(3); 
        for(int i=0;i<3;i++) sb.append((char)(48+ans));
        return ans!=-1? sb.toString() : "";
     }

