Logic:
we are simply checking 3 consecutive numbers first, if every number is same. then we proceed, else not.
we simply find the integer value of these 3 digits. and according to the max value we found in this process. we store its corresponding string in our final ans string variable.

```
string largestGoodInteger(string num) {
		//CD stands for current candidate, fs is final string ans.
        string cd="",fs="";
		//Current string val, final string val.
        int cv=0,fv=0;

        for(int i=2;i<=num.size()-1;i++){
           //Checking all 3 values, if equal then we proceed.
		if(num[i-2]==num[i-1]&&num[i-1]==num[i]){
                cd=cd+num[i-2]+num[i-1]+num[i];
				//Taking out the int value of the string to compare and store our result.
				//Its like finding the maximum value in an array.
                cv=stoi(cd);

				//If the current value is greater than final string value, change final string.
                if(cv>=fv){
                    fv=cv;
                    fs=cd;
                    cv=0;

                }
				//Clearing the string variable for next iteration.
                    cd="";
            }
        }        
		//Returning ans at last.
        return fs;
    }

```


