My first idea was Binary Search to find the first index which satisfy the max of [0, index] >= k.
And the complexity will be n * log(n) * log(n), it can't pass the test case with python.
Then by thinking of the detail of segment tree udpate and query,  I found out I can do the pruning during the update process. (easy to prune left child if left child has a max < k).
